text:
Cullybackey or Cullybacky () is a small village in County Antrim, Northern Ireland. It has got lots of cafes and a very good pub. It has won Britain in bloom for 4 years running.
It is a predominantly Protestant area, and host the twelfth every 3 years.
There are 2 schools, one is the Buick Memorial Primary School and the other is Cullybackey High School.
